<span id="freeTextContainer5725399070562641541">A flamenco dancer in Chicago..... what more do you need for a fantastic premise to a book? In truth, the story gets a little old, and there&apos;s definitely not enough details about the actual dancing for my taste (too many details about the typical drunken revelry of an &quot;artist&apos;s life&quot;)... but Carmen, the main character, grew on me as she grew into herself. I really enjoyed Ana Castillo&apos;s writing style, so, even if this book doesn&apos;t rank among my favorites, it&apos;s a lead-in to Castillo&apos;s other books.</span>
