<span id="freeTextContainer11291803643640282398">I haven&apos;t finished this book yet but the author speaks in a unique voice. The book reads like a Tella Novella. The heroine is likeable and the idea of a crippled flamenco dancer is sort of hard to believe. Her romantic exploits, time with her family, and career issues are all believable and poignant. Overall, I’d recommend this novel.</span>
  <span id="freeText11291803643640282398" style="display:none">I haven't finished this book yet but the author speaks in a unique voice. The book reads like a Tella Novella. The heroine is likeable and the idea of a crippled flamenco dancer is sort of hard to believe. Her romantic exploits, time with her family, and career issues are all believable and poignant. Overall, I’d recommend this novel.</span>
